reviews.text: Last minute Super Bowl plans for a home party and the Wingstop App made for a clutch combo. They were fairly organized and I’m a sucker for the boneless wings. It does the job!
A latina girl and Dwain, have very high service standards, they make me feel order everyday, thanks for the good vibes :D
This place is disrespectfull, all the time i have to wait 20 min to pickup my order. Any other restaurant around would be quicker. Im not comming back
I got food poisoning from this location. Very disrespectful staff. Especially the bigger girl that works the register.
Love the combos here....

reviews.text:
Still the greatest authentic tacos.
And reasonable on top of it. Good service great salsa and overall a great place for Mexican food. I have been coming here for years now. Almost 20 years and its still just as good as when they started .
I had the 3 chicken taco special with guacamole.  Very filling and under 9 $ with tax.

Ordered through the app. Guac was brown and sour (maybe rotten 🤮), lettuce was brown and also had a funky flavor. I was so hungry and didn’t want to wait for a new order. So, I removed the guac and lettuce.

This is the second time the guac has been rotten or old. Many times (not this time) my order is wrong or missing something.

I want to give 5 stars because it’s available and staff seem nice, just not on top of it with the quality of the product. The food gets to me quite quickly as well, which is wonderful.

I’d love to change my stars to five but need to see more consistency in the quality of service and product.

Cheers!

We visited there on 29 August after a 4-year absence.  Their Burrito was definitely one of the best in the area:  their Carnitas was superb; you could choose regular, spinach or chilli tortilla; pinto or black beans or both; they offered 6-7 types of salsas from the separate counter.  The filling was generous and the flavour wonderful.  They had two men singing Mexican songs in the evning and we had a good time.  We tried others in the area, but we will stick with this one.  The only gripe was the rest room.  Can they do something about it???
Great service and great comfort food. I tried their cauliflower rice, not much if a fan of it but their chicken is fantastic

Chicken Burrito - white rice, black beans, pico, corn, cheese, guacamole, and lettuce

Ingredients were fresher and more generous than most chipotles. Satisfied!

reviews.text: This spot if the best, we love getting to do breakfast here. They also have super good milkshakes. I usually get their Pancake combo and let me tell ya the pancakes are big. Their staff is super friendly and they treat you right. Gotta check this fun diner out and see all of their cool decor.

Stopped by here on a whim one night. Felt like milkshake!

Staff is friendly!
Service is fast.
Food looks great
Milkshake/malt was delicous.
Price is mildly higher.

I was able to look at the decor that made this place and really enjoyed it.
I'd like to get some food from here in the future or next time I'm in LA.

The BEST milkshake in Southern California.
I can have breakfast at any time of the day, and this lovely diner food holds up.

Don't expect "healthy" food - this is a diner. Everything is delicious and bad for you. 😈

I think I could scream it until I'm blue in the face, this is the best place for milkshakes. Hands down.

Pat's is a solid choice for breakfast/brunch and the line doesn't get too crazy. I know everyone usually likes to go to Mama's nearby, which don't get me wrong is delicious in itself, but Pat's is also a heavy contender on the North Beach brunch scene! The decor is really cute with local artwork on the walls and plenty of colorful flowers.

This place is SOOOOOO good! From the service to the taste of the food. I ordered a few things to share with my friend and her daughters and we were all very happy with the food. One of the best Mediterranean restaurants in the area.

reviews.text: My friend & I were craving thai food & found this place when in the area. The place does get busy so I do suggest coming in with time. The service was great! Our server was so nice & food tasted so good. The portions coudlvd been more but we still loved the food. I would still recommend this place since the food taste so good and the servers make great recommendations if its your first time there.

We are so sad Mar Vista location has closed. This is by far our favorite Thai restaurant. Great food, great service, the surroundings in SM location are poor. We hope you will return to the Palms-Culver-Westchester area soon.
Very kind staff and great food and good prices. Much enjoyed.
Best Thai food I've had in a long time!

This is a must-try spot in CA however, be prepared to wait in line. The dry fried wings are some of the best chicken wings I've had in my life but unfortunately that's not enough for a 4 star experience.

reviews.text: Terrific place.  All you can eat style buffet for about $13.  There's also a bar (which I've never seen people use).  Comfy chairs, booths, tables and utensils.  It's the type of place you should dress at least semi-professionally.  Evening dining is also very pleasant because they light candles (I've only been here at evening once, I usually come for the lunch buffet).  Prices are very reasonable and there's a parking garage adjacent to it as well, so parking is not a problem.  It's a nice place to bring your parents or a date.

I go to this special restaurant many times  as I like the ambiance that is part of this place. The team is very welcoming and experienced. The service is very fast. Needless to say, the food they prepare is highly distinguished. I visited often and I was always joyful. The rate is decent. I recommend this restaurant to to everybody.
Great food! If you want good Indian, go here. You won’t be disappointed. Staff is very friendly as well.

I celebrated my graduation this evening in this delicious restaurant. I am glad to say that we enjoyed a superb evening and the restaurant was clearly one of the reasons for the strong evening. The stuff  helped in a lovely manner, the meals were delicious and my guests were extremely  thrilled. We shall absolutely return for more joyful events. thanks very much.
Super appetizing. I look forward to going back again. This place has a good feel to it. If it was closer to my home I would be here often.

reviews.text: Service was nice as well. Our waiter was cracking jokes and making us laugh, giving us recommendations for our orders. He was attentive. It's a $$ restaurant so price and portions were very adequate. I will come back again next time I'm in the downtown area.

I like this restaurant! They have first-cleass meals, they have a nice menu, The chief cook in that restaurant is very trained, I enjoy very much tasting all their dishes. The dishes are always good, the service towards the customers  is agreeable. I often go to  this restaurant and I was never unsatisfied. I recommend it to all.

We arrived at this spot for dinner. my friend recommended this spot.  Well, we were not disappointed. the staff members were so friendly and we felt excellent. The food was just great. We loved this restaurant a lot and we shall definitely come back again. Recommended.
I adore this place very much. there is a friendly spirit. The food is superb. the service is powerful and the crew is trained. The cost is modest. truly recommend.

This place is so great!  Such a classic, iconic, and traditional family-run local Italian restaurant!  It's complete with the dark interior and red leather booths with pictures of Guido and all of the movie stars that have visited his place over the years!  Their house salad is so great with the pancetta.   The only reason why I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 is because my shrimp had a bit of a freezer-thawed taste to it.  It is also pretty pricey here.  Because of Covid they have seating outside in the parking lot under a tent.  I'll be back!

All about$  overcharges for delivery or no contact not senior friendly.
Nice thai food service it was 5 Stars.👍

The staff were very attentive and friendly which was a plus.  The addition of a private parking lot in the back for a restaurant on Sunset was huge too.  I am very curious to come back and try other dishes because I feel the ones I chose were not of my particular preference.

the red curry is my absolute favorite in LA. i always add pineapple too, which makes is super sweet. Always a great price.
I love this place!

reviews.text: I’ve been craving a pizza. Good thing I bumped into this pizza pub. I didn’t know that they served such a delicious and mouthwatering pizza. This pizza pub is my new favorite place in this area. The place was so neat and clean. The staff was so welcoming and friendly.  The food served quickly which I like the most. I will surely recommend this place to my friends.

Total from Postmates for this personal pizza that was a little bigger than my hand and a Diet Coke - $17. This isn’t including delivery.
You guys...this pizza was inedible. It had the consistency of a stale crouton and tore up the roof of my mouth.

This place was bomb. You can get a huge slice of pizza for like $4.50. Cant really beat that. Good variety to choose from, definitely unique pizza compared to others. Customer service is good too. Definitely recommend.
Excellent service & cuisine. What a gem! Locally sourced. Such an awesome spot with an ever changing menu.

This pizza is so fire I haTe that there's none by my house but I like it betteer than blaze pizza or pizza rev. It's so soft and the meats have a better taste. I used to always come here cause it was close to my job now I only come if I'm in the area, they have beer & desserts too and the cream soda is my fav.

reviews.text: First-rate environment and super friendly service. The menu was fresh and delicious. Will definitely recommend this place to anyone. Fair prices and big meals. Great job.

After having read many great reviews and judgments about this restaurant, we had high expectations. These were indeed matched! The food is superb, probably the best we have ever had in this city. The servers are also very friendly and accommodating to our needs. I will return to this restaurant for business meetings in the future.

Best pizza around! Fresh and delicious! Ordered through grubhub for the first time and I'm in heaven!!! Thanks guys

Ok so I ordered the subs this time...philly cheesesteak and New York steak sub

Philly was amazing, the New York steak was ok since I think they used the same meat that is in philly and not an actual ny steak but overal fresh, fast and yummy!!! Delivery guy was professional and sweet
Keep up the good work! Will be ordering again and again as long as you guys are keeping it up :)

Ordered hot wings-they are to die for!

This is one of my favorite go-to Italian restaurants. The staff are always so friendly, the ambience is so lively, and the food is amazing. I always say that I will try something new but inevitably end up getting the gnocchi and beef carpacio.

I love that it's a small, upscale space that is good for dates, lunches, and families. They really cater to whatever you're looking for.

I haven't used it, but I believe there's also a small room that can be rented out for private gatherings, which helps take you away from the noise and bustle of the restaurant if you want something more intimate.

Have been countless times, will always return when I'm in LA.

Ugh I just love this place. The prices went a little up but their pasta is unbelievable good. I had the ravioli Sith pumpkin and sweet potato and it was absolutely amazing. We come here and share 4 different kind of pasta with two people just because it's so good.

reviews.text: One of my favorite places to grab something to eat. excellent location, clean, and awesome service. Very good job!

The food was amazing! My family came for my mom's birthday and our server, Bubbly, was so sweet and kind. The food portions were very filling. We will definitely come back again. Thanks again, Bubbly for the great service!
I give this spot two thumbs up. Next time I'll be back with my coworkers. Bring your appetite because portions are filling.

We arrived at this place for a meeting. we heard about this restaurant from a lot of people.  Well, it was a winning. The staff welcomed us with a smile and we felt good. The food was just great. We loved this restaurant very much and we will visit this place again. we highly recommend this place.
The staff was very welcoming and sociable. It has a cool atmosphere.

reviews.text: The food is consistently well prepared and yummy, employees hands over awesome customer service. I really like how clean it is and atmosphere. Highly recommended.

Really clean place. Cat did me a favor by introducing me to my new favorite drink called the Paper Plane, which Ani made so ask her to make it next time you go! Also, never had to wait for more than a second to order food and more drinks because Araxy was always super close and super attentive. If you love cheese then Macaroni and cheese will never taste the same once you've had it here you will always crave the Oak and Vine's

Last week was our first time we visited this excellent restaurant. But It is definitely not the last time. We had a good time with the courteous service, with the superb  cuisine and fine drinks and with the honest price. We will definitely visit there soon.

Freshly prepared food with authentic taste.  They do not add a lot of flavor outside the natural flavors of food, and I know some Americans want Panda Express style junk food, but this place is delicious, fresh, and authentic.  Great fish dishes, and their traditional dishes are also excellent.
Westlake beef soup, eggplant with shredded pork, pork chop with spicy salt always a must.  The variety, quality and portions are great.

reviews.text: I adore this place! They serve high quality food, their menu is varied, The chief cook in that place is well trained, I enjoy a lot trying all their dishes. The dishes are consistently fresh and tasty, the service towards the visitors  is helpful. I visit often this place and I was never unsatisfied. I recommend it to all my friends.
The seafood was very fresh and well prepared. The Ahi Tuna was very flavorful. Justin was our waiter and he did a great job taking care of us. We will definitely ask for him next time.

Everyone was so kind and wanted to make everything perfect! The food came out really fast which was great because we were very hungry. My dad was a little overwhelmed with how spicy the wings were! Perfect if your a super spicy person. If you come here definitely try the sauces especially the sweet and sour sauces.
The foods here are very delicious. Fresh and well cooked. I always eat here every time I have the chance to stop by.

We came to this restaurant for a meeting. This place was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, we were not disappointed. The crew were very polite and we had a great feeling. The meal was delicious. We enjoyed every moment and we will visit this place again. We recommend this place to all.

reviews.text: Love this hidden Gem. We went for a light dinner and really enjoyed the fresh, unique food. Excellent staff and reasonably priced in Los Angeles, CA.
Such a great spot for takeout sushi! Best avocado roll
Great staff, and quick, quality food.  Try both the veggie and the pork gyoza.  Have not yet tried the ramen, but will.  Also great cucumber salad.

Low rating primarily because of the service. Order for pickup took over an hour to prepare. I was quoted 30-40 mins on the phone because their online ordering was down.
Sushi was ok. Salmon, eel, and shellfish were good. Yellowtail and tuna were underwhelming.
Great restaurant nice selection of sushi and yummy food very fair price.will definitely keep on coming.

reviews.text: I really enjoyed my experience at Papa John’s with Felix he’s a wonderful person and it’s an asset to the company he helped me patiently and took care of my concerns and provided an excellent hospitality and customer service especially especially during COVID-19. Thank you. If you haven’t experience him, just ask for him.
Good food, nice staff. High quality food. Recommend calling ahead then show up maybe 2min early

Amazing place!  If this spot was in my neighborhood, I'd be there all the time. Made a point of seeking this place out, and will do again next time we're in CA. Staff was super friendly.  Pizza was ridiculous.  Great place.
Love that their Pizza is handmade. It was done in 15 minutes.

Got a large, two topping pizza for lunch. Two sodas, extra garlic sauce. Like 16 something. Not bad split between two people. Ate it there with a coworker. Really hot and fresh. Place is seemingly really clean and nice inside. One of the better ones I've been in, actually. Lady employee was friendly. NICE!

reviews.text: The food is always delicious, the staff is super friendly and the service is quick! One of my favorite dishes is the Green Curry. Their Coronavirus safety measures are the best I've seen at any restaurant. It very quickly became my go-to Thai place.
They offer a vast variety of fresh food. I enjoyed dining here. The employees are always kind, pricing is affordable and the place is always clean.

This is such an awesome hidden little spot! All of the dishes we’ve tried here have been amazing and probably some of the best Thai I’ve had.

Their customer service is absolutely incredible.

In terms of COVID safety, I think they’ve got the best setup I’ve seen. There’s a waiting area that has a payment area, a designated spot where they put your order, and they have hand sanitizer too.

Pad Thai flavor wasn’t quite right and lacking egg.
The packaging is heavy on plastic! They don’t even try.
Great food and excellent customer service! Chase was my cashier and was super friendly and helpful with my order as it was my first time. Highly recommend!

reviews.text:
Worst customer service! The guy I was talking to was yelling at me. Literally yelling wouldn't let me speak. Talk about it's lunch hour. I'm a customer too. I'm here to order food why are you rushing me. He was working 12pm on 11/20/20. Try to avoid this tome unless you want someone to ruin your day.
So disappointed

Asked for the manager (looked Indian). Didn’t allow me to get 8 thighs and when I asked why he said that they didn’t have enough but the grill was full  of chicken. I wanted to do more of the order of eight soups with the extra rice beans the whole shebang but apparently the manager didn’t want to sell me it. I work for a hospital I will not recommend this specific the store to cater from. And don’t ask me to revise.

I have a food allergy to dairy. Staff also got a  lady in front order wrong. Two orders wrong in a row. How does this happen. An apology was given. Anyways staff replaced my order. I'll definitely come back, but will make sure my order is read to me
The Soup at this place is tasteless and no chicken at all. It's just like hot water with veggies. I have ordered it many times but it's the same all the times. New Chef Perhaps Will Do.
The customer service is regularly speedy, fantastic character, helpful staff members. Will return here again when I am in the area.

reviews.text: We love to go out. Last night we  visited this magnificent restaurant which friends recommended to us. We spent a beautiful time there with fine meal and a professional stuff and a distinguished  chef. We put this venue in our list  and we will no doubt visit again soon. We warmly recommend.

Really good service and overall a good experience.  I ordered the Mix Sushi and my brother ordered the Mix Sashimi.  For $25 each, we both got a decent amount of fish, as well as a good miso soup and salad.  The service was quite great as well.  Perhaps if there was a little bit less of that shredded daikon in the sashimi that would have been better, but overall very pleased with En Sushi.  They have outdoor dining too!

Went here for the first time, Very Impressed! The food that was prepared in front of us was absolutely delicious. The chefs that worked are table were very talkative, friendly and entertaining. The place is a little pricey, but you get what you pay for.

I've heard so many good things about this place, so I decided to try myself. The place is small, but very intimat. Style is very Japanese. The most important part. They make handrolls very fast and right in front of you. The fish is super fresh and delicious.
I constantly stop purchasing some food in this spot. I enjoy the quick customer service and well made dishes. Keep it up.

reviews.text: A delicious, fun spot with great atmosphere, yummy drinks and great food! Had brunch with my friends on Sunday and absolutely loved it! Definitely coming back!
Good food and good service. I also liked some of the cocktails

On Wilshire - Love the interior design, monitors everywhere to watch music videos and sports events, friendly wait staff and bartenders who take care of you.
Best deals during happy hour!
Avoid the rush and crowd, come early.

I had a delicious cocktail they've named La Lambada - leblon cachaca, mezcal, lime, jalapeño tincture, and mole bitters, garnished with red sweet pepper. It had a kick, but was definitely not overwhelming. A really well balanced and thought out concoction. $10.

Great resturant there is only about 10 parking spaces but it's a really good spot. Happy hour is from 4pm to 8pm on Tuesdays I believe not sure. Check it out you wont be disappointed did not look at the prices but it was worth it.

reviews.text: This site is my preferable site.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to this restaurant. Whenever  I want to go to a superb lunch, this place comes immediately to my mind. very good and varied  food and a rich menu.generous staff, and good mood. In addition to that, the tariff is affordable. I suggest this place with no hesitation.
Typical sub sandwiches, I always order the special of the day. Prefer the foot long when I'm hungry.

There are always friendly staff and I appreciate the fact that they are open 24/7. The Las time I was there I ordered a meatball marinara and I don't know if it's just me or if the quality in taste of the meatballs has been going down hill. I ordered a foot long and I really didn't enjoy it. The meatballs were just off a bit.
Please don't eat this sandwiches, I had a chicken and bacon sandwich and  I got a food poison.
I love the wraps at subway. Great staff friendly and professional

reviews.text: Visiting this Coco’s location is literally the reason I came to Cali for the first time. We’ve eaten twice here in the past 3 days. If you’ve been to Tokyo, the LA USA locations are just as good as in Tokyo. Just wish they had garlic bits. Also recommend the Chicken Cutlets, they’re the best to try first. Highly highly recommend this restaurant for an amazing taste of Japan!
This place is delicious. I always come here since it is local to my office. Thanks guys!
I love the Japanese food here! I wish I could spend my valentines here with my date
Love this place! Great curry, humble people, very clean
We love us our Japanese curry! Takes us back to living in Tokyo. Staff is always attentive and friendly.
